China reiterated its "one country, two systems" approach to Taiwan while unveiling its anti-secession law.
MAC Deputy Chairman Chiu Tai-shan criticized Beijing's plan, warning of potential military action.
President Chen Shui-bian condemned the law as a threat to stability.
Mainland Affairs Council Chairman Joseph Wu urged Taiwan to consider a referendum on reunification terms.
The US and EU expressed concerns over the legislation, urging China to reconsider.
Legislative Yuan Speaker Wang Jin-pyng announced plans to pass a resolution opposing the law.
Overall, tensions remain high as Taiwan braces for potential changes in cross-strait relations.
